          "publishedAt": "2026-05-29T07:28:37.000Z",
          "author": "Asif Razzaq",
          "summary": "<p>Hexo Labs released SIA, an open-source self-improving loop, under an MIT license. A Feedback-Agent reads each run's trajectory, then either rewrites the scaffold or triggers a LoRA weight update on gpt-oss-120b. Combining both levers beat scaffold-only iteration on LawBench, TriMul GPU kernels, and scRNA-seq denoising.</p> <p>The post <a href=\"https://www.marktechpost.com/2026/05/29/hexo-labs-open-sources-sia-a-self-improving-agent-that-updates-both-the-harness-and-the-model-weights/\">Hexo Labs Open-Sources SIA: A Self-Improving Agent That Updates Both the Harness and the Model Weights</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.marktechpost.com\">MarkTechPost</a>.</p>",
